5685:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****           (##) Prepare synchronization configuration necessary for HSI48 calibration
5686:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****               (+++) Default values can be set for frequency Error Measurement (reload and error lim
5687:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****                         and also HSI48 oscillator smooth trimming.
5688:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****               (+++) Macro __HAL_RCC_CRS_RELOADVALUE_CALCULATE can be also used to calculate
5689:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****                         directly reload value with target and synchronization frequencies values
5690:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****           (##) Call function HAL_RCCEx_CRSConfig which
5691:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****               (+++) Resets CRS registers to their default values.
5692:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****               (+++) Configures CRS registers with synchronization configuration
5693:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****               (+++) Enables automatic calibration and frequency error counter feature
5694:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****            Note: When using USB LPM (Link Power Management) and the device is in Sleep mode, the
5695:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****            periodic USB SOF will not be generated by the host. No SYNC signal will therefore be
5696:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****            provided to the CRS to calibrate the HSI48 on the run. To guarantee the required clock
5697:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****            precision after waking up from Sleep mode, the LSE or reference clock on the GPIOs
5698:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_rcc_ex.c ****            should be used as SYNC signal.
